 taught this way. There are advantages to int main(), but people aren't always taught that.", "id": "e4zcdq9", "replies": [{"body": "The standard type signatures for main all return int; that's why it matters.", "id": "e4zciiq", "replies": [{"body": "I've done a fair bit of googling, and I stand corrected. I always have used int main() and taught others to use it as well, just never knew the specifics. I also learned about the more proper int main(void), for programs similar to OPs.", "id": "e4zd0z0", "replies": []}]}]}]}], "title": "This code is crashing CodeBlocks IDE..."}